  "prompt": "What are the most famous things in Varanasi?",
  "response": "Varanasi, also known as Banaras or Kashi, is famous for several things:\n\n1. Ghats\n- Dashashwamedh Ghat\n- Manikarnika Ghat (famous burning/cremation ghat)\n- Assi Ghat\n\n2. Religious Significance\n- Kashi Vishwanath Temple\n- Spiritual center for Hindus\n- Important pilgrimage destination\n\n3. Cultural Heritage\n- Oldest continuously inhabited city in India\n- Rich cultural and historical traditions\n- Classical music and dance\n\n4. Silk Weaving\n- Banarasi silk sarees\n- Traditional handloom weaving\n\n5. Spiritual Practices\n- Evening Ganga Aarti\n- Boat rides on River Ganges\n- Meditation and yoga centers\n\n6. Historical Landmarks\n- Alamgir Mosque\n- Durga Temple\n- Bharat Kala Bhavan Museum\n\n7. Classical Learning\n- Banaras Hindu University\n- Center for Sanskrit and classical studies\n\n8. Food\n- Banarasi paan\n- Local street food\n- Traditional sweets and cuisine\n\nThese elements make Varanasi a unique and culturally significant city in India.",
